( 4. Rationale and generalization) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The heuristic model is transparent and easy to convert into policy. The Isolation Forest) Tj
T*
(model catches multivariate oddities that a small rule set may miss. Both should) Tj
T*
(generalize when bot traffic is repetitive or mechanically timed, but they may miss) Tj
T*
(human-like bots and may over-flag legitimate campaigns that naturally produce high) Tj
T*
(repetition. The thresholds should be recalibrated when traffic mix, geography, or ad) Tj
T*
(inventory changes materially.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 5. Probability assessment) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The estimated probability that a flagged event is fraudulent is 77%. This is not label-) Tj
T*
(calibrated precision; it is a reasoned estimate based on agreement between independent) Tj
T*
(signals. Events flagged by both the heuristic model and the upper tail of the ML anomaly) Tj
T*
(score are more likely to be fraudulent than events flagged by only one weak signal. The) Tj
T*
(report therefore treats probability as an operational confidence estimate, not a) Tj
T*
(measured ground truth metric.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 6. Recommended actions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Assuming false positives and false negatives are roughly equal in cost, the submitted) Tj
T*
(binary prediction uses the combined score threshold rather than only the highest-) Tj
T*
(confidence intersection. For business action, use three tiers: suppress bot events with) Tj
T*
(the strongest combined, heuristic, or heuristic/ML agreement signals; quarantine the) Tj
T*
(remaining bot events for review; and monitor traffic that is not selected for bot action) Tj
T*
(while retaining it for drift checks and future labels.) Tj
T*
